.TH TIMBRE 1 "September 2025" "timbre 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
timbre \- Smart log filtering and categorization tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B timbre
[\fIOPTION\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Timbre is a high-performance log processing tool that filters and categorizes
log output using regex patterns. It reads from stdin and sorts log messages
into appropriate categories based on configurable patterns.
.PP
Timbre provides smart log filtering with regex support, organized log
categorization into separate files, TOML configuration support, and detailed
diagnostics.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR=\fIFILE\fR
Use configuration file FILE instead of the default
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose output
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress stdout output (only write to log files)
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-append\fR
Append to existing log files instead of truncating
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display help message and exit
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Display version information and exit
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/timbre/timbre.toml
System-wide configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.config/timbre/timbre.toml
User configuration file
.TP
.I ./timbre.toml
Local configuration file (highest priority)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Process logs with default settings:
.B ./app | timbre
.TP
Use custom configuration:
.B ./app | timbre --config=custom.toml
.TP
Enable verbose output:
.B ./app | timbre --verbose
.TP
Quiet mode (no stdout):
.B ./app | timbre --quiet
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 2
Configuration error
